## Test IDs

Many testing libraries allow targeting the `data-testid` attribute to locate elements on the page to use for assertions or actions. 
AG Grid provides support for attaching this attribute to many of the interactive elements in the grid. This is achieved by registering the `TestingModule`. This module should only be used in a test or development environment, not in production.

```js
import { TestingModule, ModuleRegistry } from 'ag-grid-community'

ModuleRegistry.registerModules([TestingModule]);
```

The test ID attribute that is targeted by this module can be optionally customised using the following module method:

```js
import { TestingModule, ModuleRegistry } from 'ag-grid-community'

ModuleRegistry.registerModules([
    TestingModule.with({ testIdAttribute: 'data-customattr' })
]);
```

In addition, utility functions are provided to avoid users having to manually construct the IDs:
```js
import { agTestIdFor } from 'ag-grid-community';

// ...in your test case:
const rowId = 'toyota-celica';
const colId = 'ag-Grid-SelectionColumn';
expect(findByTestId(agTestIdFor.checkbox(rowId, colId))).toBeVisible();
```

